Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.api

Class KernelStatement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.api.CloseableResourceManager
      • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.api.KernelStatement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Resource, AssertOpen, ResourceTracker, Statement
    public class KernelStatement
extends CloseableResourceManager
implements Statement, AssertOpen
    A resource efficient implementation of Statement. Designed to be reused within a KernelTransactionImplementation instance, even across transactions since this instances itself doesn't hold essential state. Usage:
    1. Construct KernelStatement when KernelTransactionImplementation is constructed
    2. For every transaction...
    3. Call initialize(StatementLocks, PageCursorTracer, long) which makes this instance full available and ready to use. Call when the KernelTransactionImplementation is initialized.
    4. Alternate acquire() / close() when acquiring / closing a statement for the transaction... Temporarily asymmetric number of calls to acquire() / close() is supported, although in the end an equal number of calls must have been issued.
    5. To be safe call forceClose() at the end of a transaction to force a close of the statement, even if there are more than one current call to acquire(). This instance is now again ready to be initialize(StatementLocks, PageCursorTracer, long) initialized} and used for the transaction instance again, when it's initialized.
